<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 8:00PM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...LINE OF STRONG STORMS THIS EVENING...
A narrow line of strong storms will cross southern New England
between 9 PM and midnight. The main concerns are brief damaging
wind gusts of up to 60 mph. Isolated damage to trees and power
lines are possible. Brief heavy downpours could also lead to
ponding of water on roadways.
If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Do not
drive through flooded roadways.</description>
